{
  "doc_id": "31300",
  "text": "The Late-Life Function and Disability Instrument (LLFDI) was used as a comprehensive assessment of 2 disablement constructs: functional limitations (altered ability to perform specific actions encountered in daily routines) and disability (altered performance of major life tasks and social roles). [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] The functional component evaluates self-reported difficulty in performing 32 physical activities, which comprise 3 domains: upper extremity, basic lower extremity, and advanced lower extremity. The disability component evaluates self-reported limitation (capability) and frequency (performance) of taking part in 16 major life tasks. The raw scores from each item response are transformed into linear scaled scores (0 to 100) and subsequently summed to represent component and domain values.",
